<subSubSection pageId="131" pageNumber="132" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="131.[189,303,267,293]" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="131.[189,1399,313,481]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">
The species was only known previously from 
<collectingCountry box="[755,859,313,339]" name="Thailand" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Thailand</collectingCountry>
and is recorded here for the first time from 
<collectingCountry box="[189,308,349,375]" name="Singapore" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Singapore</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[364,475,349,375]" name="Malaysia" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Shamshev &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2004" box="[486,660,349,375]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Stilpon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laawae">
<emphasis box="[486,660,349,375]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Stilpon laawae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shamshev &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2004" box="[837,970,349,375]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Stilpon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seeluang">
<emphasis box="[837,970,349,375]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">S. seeluang</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group and, currently it is the only member of this unit found in 
<collectingCountry box="[588,711,384,410]" name="Singapore" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Singapore</collectingCountry>
. Note that there are small differences in the structure of the male genitalia between the 
<collectingCountry box="[514,633,419,445]" name="Singapore" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Singapore</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[692,796,419,445]" name="Thailand" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Thailand</collectingCountry>
populations, but we do not think it would be them as different species.
</paragraph>
